ns3:name: Пред Общината

INFO EN: The pitcher was built in 1981-1983 from Stefan Boyadzhiev. The fountain was opened on 9th June 1983 on the occasion of 1300 years from the foundation of Bulgaria. In the project it was planned to have a playground, relaxation space and bushes pruned like the Bulgarian map. The Pitch fountain won a Guiness award for the biggest pitcher with 2, 80 meters height. On the top of the fountain there are 70 figures, made by hand from Stefan Boyadzhiev.

INFO EN: The fountain was built from white stone and at first it had two gutters. There was a sign in Arabic above the spout. It is possible that this fountain existed even before 1878 and ordered by the Turkish rulers. Because of the raising population and the livestock in 1940 it was renovated according to their needs. The gutters became fourteen plus a big one for washing bigger fabrics.
ns3:name: Белица 3

INFO EN: The Little fountain was built during the socialist regime, the 1960s to be exact. It was built from white stone which was carved by hand. The fountain itself consists of tree big rectangular plates. It is powered from two places and has 8 gutters that are bigger than the Big fountain. The overall length is 20 meters. The water debit is pretty strong. The Little fountain is situated before the Big fountain. It’s waters flow into the tree dams in the village.
ns3:name: Косара 2
